headline: Musk's politics cost Tesla over 1 million EV sales, report shows
summary:
STORY: Elon Musk’s polarizing political action since acquiring Twitter - now X - in 2022 cost Tesla more than 1 million EV sales in the United States. 

That’s according to a report from the National Bureau of Economic Research.

The findings highlight how Musk’s actions – including his role in U.S. President Donald Trump's administration – may have cost Tesla billions.

All while benefiting rival electric carmakers.

The report by Yale economists said without the “Musk partisan effect” Tesla's U.S. sales would have been between 67% and 83% higher.

Musk's political stance has alienated environmentally minded Democratic buyers and earlier this year sparked protests around the U.S. and beyond.  

:: March 29, 2025 

At this one in New York, demonstrators called for a boycott of the carmaker and for Musk to leave his “unelected” role in the Trump administration.

As Democratic-leaning buyers shifted away from Tesla, the report found, it boosted sales of competitors' electric and hybrid vehicles by up to 22%.

It underscores how deeply the electric carmaker’s fortunes are intertwined with the billionaire's persona.
